commentary: Gabriel to Imad Wasim, no run well, what's happened here?! There is a noise as this skims past the inside edge - Imad aiming a flick to the leg side from a full ball - he's been given caught behind and has reviewed because the ball might have clipped the stump but not dislodged the bail. Certainly a noise. Appears to be daylight as ball passes bat. Remember, given out on the field. Did it glance the pad, too? Pretty sure that has clipped the off stump but is the evidence conclusive? No Snicko or Hot Spot available, so the third umpire can only go on the pictures. This is a tough one for the third umpire...and it's overturned!
